<item>
            <title>[GEOMETRY-51] EpsilonDoublePrecisionContext allows negative &amp; NaN epsilon</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GEOMETRY-51</link>
                <project id="12321920" key="GEOMETRY">Commons Geometry</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;EpsilonDoublePrecisionContext does not validate the epsilon to be positive (0 or greater). The comparison is based on Precision.compareTo(double, double, double), which itself calls Precision.equals(double, double, double), which then compares using&#160;Math.abs(y - x) &amp;lt;= eps. If epsilon is negative or NaN, the comparison is invalid.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
